    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sesame-lean-pork-and-egg-fried-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick), with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!) and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sesame-lean-pork-and-egg-fried-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, top, tail and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Trim, then roughly chop your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sesame-lean-pork-and-egg-fried-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mince has started to brown, add your <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>and <strong>sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1 min further or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sesame-lean-pork-and-egg-fried-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Squeeze the pouch[es] of<strong> cooked long grain rice</strong> to separate the grains</p><p>Once fragrant, add your<strong> cooked long grain</strong> <strong>rice</strong>,<strong> soy sauce</strong>, <strong>ketjap manis </strong>and<strong> toasted sesame oil </strong>to the pan, breaking up the rice with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Give everything a good mix up until all the rice is coated</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sesame-lean-pork-and-egg-fried-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is coated, add your <strong>blanched</strong> <strong>peas</strong> and <strong>grated carrot </strong>to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min further or until the rice is piping hot and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sesame-lean-pork-and-egg-fried-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once done, turn down the heat to medium-high, push the rice to one side of the pan and crack your <strong>egg[s] </strong>into the other side</p><p>Stir the<strong> </strong>egg[s] with a wooden spoon to break the yolk[s] and cook for 1-2 min until it resembles scrambled egg, then mix it all through the rice \u2013 this is your <strong>sesame</strong> <strong>mince &</strong> <strong>egg fried rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/sesame-lean-pork-and-egg-fried-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sesame pork & egg fried rice</strong> in a bowl</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped spring onion</strong> and <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
